headlines.description: — Even without their star point guard and their coach, the Memphis Grizzlies continued their dominant play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat Clippers, tie team win mark with 8th straight

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 28 points, Miles Bridges added 21 points and eight rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Milwaukee Bucks 114-106 on Saturday night, handing the defending NBA champions their third loss in four games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Hornets hand Bucks 3rd loss in last 4 games, 114-106

headlines.description: — Trey Lyles scored eight of his 16 points in the fourth quarter and the Detroit Pistons won for the third time in five games, beating the Orlando Magic 97-92 on Saturday night in a matchup of the NBA's two worst teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons beat Magic 97-92 in matchup of NBA's 2 worst teams

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored a career-high 42 points on 18-of-22 shooting to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 125-113 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis scores career-high 42 to Pacers past Jazz, 125-113

events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown had 22 points, 11 assists and 11 rebounds for his first career triple-double, Jayson Tatum scored 19 points and the Boston Celtics beat the New York Knicks 99-75 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown's first triple-double leads Celtics over Knicks, 99-75

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro had his best scoring game of the season. Duncan Robinson did, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat ride hot shooting to 123-100 win over the Suns
